

        // SORTING

Sorting refers to arranging the elements in the data-structure in any of the two orders, either Ascending or Descending Order.

sorting can be classified into 2 types stable sort and unstable sort

stable sort is when the order of similar elements coming in does not change..

unstable sort is when the order of similar elements coming in changes..


internal and external sorting

internal sorting : takes place inside the main memory of the computer

external sorting : takes place in the hard disk of the computer


In-place and not In-place sorting

In-place sorting sorts the elements in the same array,

while not In-place sorting sorts the elements by creating a auxiliary space array.

